WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.866 --> 00:00:03.600
Not long ago,

00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:05.333
I singled out the most frequently asked

00:00:05.333 --> 00:00:06.700
and typical questions in the comment section

00:00:06.700 --> 00:00:09.300
and did a skin care Q&amp;A session.

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:12.200
As a result, I received even more questions.

00:00:12.333 --> 00:00:13.433
One friend asked whether

00:00:13.433 --> 00:00:16.433
the small molecule hyaluronic acid advertised by merchants

00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:18.500
really has the effect of filling the skin

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:21.133
, and whether it can fight aging as the merchants claim.

00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:22.266
Another friend asked

00:00:22.266 --> 00:00:25.700
that hyaluronic acid, once hailed as one of the three major anti-aging ingredients, is

00:00:25.833 --> 00:00:29.433
now said to be only capable of repairing but not fighting aging.

00:00:29.433 --> 00:00:30.933
Who is right?

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:32.266
A third friend asked

00:00:32.266 --> 00:00:34.300
that he used two skin care products but

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:35.466
ended up with a paste.

00:00:35.466 --> 00:00:37.266
Was it a waste

00:00:37.266 --> 00:00:39.500
? How can I identify and avoid

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.400
the problem of paste

00:00:41.400 --> 00:00:42.466
when these two products are combined

00:00:42.533 --> 00:00:45.333
? I think these three questions are quite representative,

00:00:45.333 --> 00:00:47.833
so I decided to give you an additional session. Let's

00:00:47.833 --> 00:00:50.433
explain these three questions clearly today.

00:00:57.233 --> 00:00:59.300
Hello everyone, I'm the formulator Xingxing.

00:00:59.300 --> 00:01:01.533
Let's talk about the first question:

00:01:01.533 --> 00:01:04.200
hyaluronic acid. Let me first briefly explain to you

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:05.333
what hyaluronic

00:01:05.533 --> 00:01:06.233
acid

00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:08.533
is. Hyaluronic acid is widely present in our body.

00:01:08.533 --> 00:01:09.666
Just like our eyeballs

00:01:09.666 --> 00:01:11.333
, they are crystal clear

00:01:11.333 --> 00:01:14.500
because the vitreous body is full of hyaluronic acid.

00:01:14.666 --> 00:01:16.933
What about the joints in our body?

00:01:16.933 --> 00:01:20.100
The reason they are so smooth when we exercise

00:01:20.133 --> 00:01:22.666
is because they are full of hyaluronic acid

00:01:22.666 --> 00:01:23.866
as a lubricant.

00:01:23.900 --> 00:01:25.500
Our skin is also

00:01:25.500 --> 00:01:27.000
one of the skins of young people.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.066
So the reason why it looks full, plump

00:01:29.066 --> 00:01:30.033
and translucent

00:01:30.033 --> 00:01:33.066
is because it contains a lot of hyaluronic acid.

00:01:33.266 --> 00:01:35.233
As we age,

00:01:35.233 --> 00:01:38.266
our hyaluronic acid will gradually break down and be lost,

00:01:38.266 --> 00:01:42.100
and our ability to produce hyaluronic acid will decline.

00:01:42.233 --> 00:01:43.300
The consequences

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:45.333
are that our eyes will not be as bright,

00:01:45.333 --> 00:01:46.266
and our joints

00:01:46.266 --> 00:01:48.533
will creak when we move.

00:01:48.533 --> 00:01:51.300
The skin will look less plump and

00:01:51.300 --> 00:01:53.633
even dry, loose and sagging.

00:01:53.633 --> 00:01:54.833
This is why

00:01:54.833 --> 00:01:57.266
hyaluronic acid is a very important ingredient

00:01:57.266 --> 00:01:59.500
in skincare products.

00:01:59.500 --> 00:02:00.866
In the beginning,

00:02:00.866 --> 00:02:01.833
scientists thought

00:02:01.833 --> 00:02:03.666
that they could use

00:02:03.666 --> 00:02:05.033
the hyaluronic acid

00:02:05.033 --> 00:02:08.133
in our body as an ingredient in skincare products

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:10.733
. If you absorb it, it will replenish your skin.

00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:13.000
But they soon discovered a problem.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:14.866
The hyaluronic acid

00:02:14.866 --> 00:02:15.733
in our body has

00:02:15.733 --> 00:02:18.133
a very large molecular weight of

00:02:18.200 --> 00:02:21.200
1.5 million to several million daltons.

00:02:21.300 --> 00:02:22.866
When it is applied to the skin,

00:02:22.866 --> 00:02:25.233
it can only stay on the surface of your skin

00:02:25.233 --> 00:02:26.866
and cannot be absorbed

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:28.266
. Why can't it be absorbed?

00:02:28.266 --> 00:02:29.266
It's like

00:02:29.266 --> 00:02:32.266
my hyaluronic acid with a molecular weight of several million

00:02:32.266 --> 00:02:33.466
is like an elephant

00:02:33.466 --> 00:02:35.900
, and the gaps in your skin are only the size of a mouse hole.

00:02:36.033 --> 00:02:39.500
It's impossible for an elephant to fit through a mouse hole,

00:02:39.633 --> 00:02:41.100
so it can't be absorbed.

00:02:41.266 --> 00:02:43.666
Then scientists started to think again.

00:02:43.666 --> 00:02:45.100
Since our skin is so large

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:47.400
, They tried to cut it into smaller pieces,

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:49.233
using enzyme cutting or

00:02:49.233 --> 00:02:49.933
hydrolysis techniques.

00:02:49.933 --> 00:02:51.033
Regardless of the technology,

00:02:51.033 --> 00:02:54.466
they ultimately managed to cut it into very small pieces.

00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:56.300
Current hyaluronic acid production processes

00:02:56.300 --> 00:02:58.400
can achieve a minimum molecular weight

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:01.866
of 500-800 Daltons. This

00:03:01.866 --> 00:03:04.833
means that if an elephant were to become a small earthworm

00:03:04.833 --> 00:03:07.266
, the mouse would definitely be able to fit into the hole.

00:03:07.266 --> 00:03:09.900
Actual scientific research has proven this

00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:12.200
: it can be absorbed into the dermis,

00:03:12.533 --> 00:03:15.500
achieving the goal of good absorption.

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:18.233
So, did this small molecule of hyaluronic acid

00:03:18.233 --> 00:03:20.600
achieve our

00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:22.833
goal of supplementing hyaluronic acid to make the skin more plump?

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:25.333
No, why not?

00:03:25.333 --> 00:03:27.200
Let me describe how

00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:29.666
hyaluronic acid works

00:03:29.666 --> 00:03:31.533
after it's absorbed into the skin.

00:03:31.800 --> 00:03:32.600
Hyaluronic acid

00:03:32.600 --> 00:03:34.400
is a very special molecule

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:38.866
that can bind 1,000 times its own weight in water molecules.

00:03:38.933 --> 00:03:39.500
That is,

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:41.233
once it enters the skin,

00:03:41.233 --> 00:03:42.466
it begins to grab

00:03:42.466 --> 00:03:43.600
water molecules

00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:45.066
until it has 1,000.

00:03:45.233 --> 00:03:46.633
Once

00:03:46.633 --> 00:03:49.733
it's full, the expanded molecule

00:03:49.733 --> 00:03:51.633
is a hyaluronic acid molecule.

00:03:51.700 --> 00:03:52.733
Imagine

00:03:52.733 --> 00:03:56.066
if the absorbed hyaluronic acid was a large molecule

00:03:56.066 --> 00:03:58.533
the size of a soccer ball, and

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:00.100
after grabbing the water molecules,

00:04:00.100 --> 00:04:02.833
it could become the size of a soccer field

00:04:02.833 --> 00:04:04.300
. Now,

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:06.033
there's a small molecule of hyaluronic acid

00:04:06.033 --> 00:04:08.200
, perhaps only the size of a mung bean.

00:04:08.200 --> 00:04:10.900
So, after grabbing 1,000 molecules, how big would it be?

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.533
One is the size of a ping-pong

00:04:12.633 --> 00:04:15.233
ball. On one side is a hyaluronic acid molecule the size of a football field,

00:04:15.233 --> 00:04:17.833
and on the other side are hyaluronic acid molecules the size of a ping-pong ball.

00:04:17.833 --> 00:04:19.233
If both are put into your skin,

00:04:19.233 --> 00:04:20.700
which one will provide better plumping

00:04:20.900 --> 00:04:23.866
? So, the scientists started thinking again.

00:04:23.866 --> 00:04:25.866
What if we had a way

00:04:25.866 --> 00:04:29.700
to pull large molecule hyaluronic acid directly into the skin

00:04:29.733 --> 00:04:31.333
? Wouldn't that solve the problem?

00:04:31.433 --> 00:04:34.133
There are three ways for substances to enter the skin

00:04:34.133 --> 00:04:36.466
: 1. Absorption through cells,

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:39.633
2. Absorption through skin appendages,

00:04:39.833 --> 00:04:43.033
and 3. Absorption through the interstitial spaces of the skin.

00:04:43.233 --> 00:04:45.533
So, if large molecules want to enter the skin...

00:04:45.533 --> 00:04:47.600
Obviously, only path 3

00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:48.500
is more reliable

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:50.300
, which is to use an external force

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:55.200
to push it in or pull it in from the skin gap.

00:04:55.433 --> 00:04:58.066
For example, there is a raw material research and development company

00:04:58.066 --> 00:04:59.933
that did something.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.500
It used the attraction between

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:04.866
positive and negative charges

00:05:04.900 --> 00:05:08.400
to pull the macromolecular hyaluronic acid into the skin.

00:05:08.433 --> 00:05:10.733
Let me explain how this is done.

00:05:10.733 --> 00:05:12.066
Our skin

00:05:12.066 --> 00:05:14.400
is positively charged inside and

00:05:14.466 --> 00:05:16.933
the surface of the skin is negatively charged.

00:05:17.033 --> 00:05:17.600
However,

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:19.800
the positive charge inside is larger than

00:05:19.800 --> 00:05:21.833
the charge on the surface of the skin.

00:05:21.833 --> 00:05:25.066
Hyaluronic acid is naturally negatively charged

00:05:25.066 --> 00:05:26.466
and not much.

00:05:26.466 --> 00:05:29.800
So when we want it to be absorbed... The negative charge

00:05:29.800 --> 00:05:32.033
on the surface of the skin

00:05:32.033 --> 00:05:34.800
repels the negative charge of the hyaluronic acid itself,

00:05:34.866 --> 00:05:36.200
making it difficult to absorb.

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:39.300
How does this special process treat hyaluronic acid?

00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:41.066
It uses a material

00:05:41.066 --> 00:05:45.400
that allows the hyaluronic acid to carry a particularly strong negative charge.

00:05:45.433 --> 00:05:46.066
At this time,

00:05:46.066 --> 00:05:49.833
the force of attraction between it and the positive and negative charges deep in the skin

00:05:49.900 --> 00:05:53.600
is greater than the repulsive force between the skin and the surface of the skin

00:05:53.800 --> 00:05:54.900
, pulling it in

00:05:55.266 --> 00:05:56.000
. This

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.933
is just one example of specialized treatment.

00:05:58.933 --> 00:06:02.333
In fact,
there are many ways to specifically treat hyaluronic acid,

00:06:02.333 --> 00:06:04.300
such as wrapping it in microcapsules

00:06:04.300 --> 00:06:07.066
, making some changes to the entire molecule,

00:06:07.066 --> 00:06:08.700
acetylation, etc.

00:06:08.700 --> 00:06:10.000
There are many ways

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.833
to apply an external force to the large molecule hyaluronic acid

00:06:12.833 --> 00:06:13.833
to push it in and

00:06:13.833 --> 00:06:14.700
pull it in.

00:06:14.933 --> 00:06:16.233
To sum up. Next

00:06:16.233 --> 00:06:18.000
, large-molecule hyaluronic acid

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:19.833
can be absorbed

00:06:19.833 --> 00:06:21.100
after special treatment.

00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:23.100
So, back to the question itself,

00:06:23.100 --> 00:06:24.500
can small-molecule hyaluronic acid

00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:27.466
make the skin more plump?

00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:28.866
The answer is no.

00:06:29.033 --> 00:06:29.733
We

00:06:29.733 --> 00:06:33.500
need to buy specially treated molecular hyaluronic acid.

00:06:33.733 --> 00:06:35.300
But for consumers,

00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:36.466
there is a difficulty here .

00:06:36.466 --> 00:06:38.066
Regardless of whether the hyaluronic acid

00:06:38.066 --> 00:06:40.533
has been specially treated or not,

00:06:40.533 --> 00:06:43.466
it is written in the formula sheet as

00:06:43.500 --> 00:06:44.600
sodium hyaluronate.

00:06:45.033 --> 00:06:46.866
In fact, it is difficult for users to distinguish.

00:06:46.866 --> 00:06:48.700
So, to provide convenience for everyone,

00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:51.000
I specially

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:54.000
collected the specially treated hyaluronic acid raw materials

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:55.300
on the market

00:06:55.333 --> 00:06:57.600
and confirmed with the raw material companies

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.900
the list of products that

00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:02.066
have added their special hyaluronic acid ingredients.

00:07:02.233 --> 00:07:03.600
Because there are too many products

00:07:03.600 --> 00:07:05.900
, I will pick out a few typical products

00:07:05.900 --> 00:07:07.733
and put them at the end of this video.

00:07:10.866 --> 00:07:11.700
The second question

00:07:11.700 --> 00:07:15.033
is whether bosera can fight aging.

00:07:15.033 --> 00:07:16.633
Before answering this question, let

00:07:16.633 --> 00:07:17.466
's first

00:07:17.466 --> 00:07:18.466
talk

00:07:18.466 --> 00:07:20.733
about the physiological mechanism of

00:07:20.733 --> 00:07:23.133
bosera after it is absorbed into our skin

00:07:23.300 --> 00:07:26.333
. If we compare our dermis to a mattress

00:07:26.333 --> 00:07:30.233
, the springs in the mattress are collagen.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:30.900
Of course,

00:07:30.900 --> 00:07:33.266
a mattress cannot have only springs,

00:07:33.266 --> 00:07:34.433
it also has to have fillings

00:07:34.433 --> 00:07:35.666
, that is, sponges.

00:07:35.800 --> 00:07:38.700
However, the springs in our skin

00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:40.866
are different from

00:07:40.866 --> 00:07:42.533
the springs and sponges in a real mattress.

00:07:42.633 --> 00:07:44.466
The springs and sponges in the skin

00:07:44.466 --> 00:07:46.533
exist in this form.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:48.733
This thread is what we call the spring,

00:07:48.733 --> 00:07:50.066
that is, collagen,

00:07:50.066 --> 00:07:52.833
and the ball on top is the sponge

00:07:52.833 --> 00:07:54.466
. It is a filler for the skin.

00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:56.500
What does

00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:58.100
bosera do when it enters the skin

00:07:58.100 --> 00:07:59.833
? It does two things.

00:07:59.866 --> 00:08:03.533
One is that it makes the filler

00:08:03.533 --> 00:08:05.733
, that is, the ball, more numerous.

00:08:05.833 --> 00:08:07.000
The other

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:09.800
is that it makes the single ball bigger.

00:08:10.133 --> 00:08:13.066
So how does bosera make the balls more numerous?

00:08:13.133 --> 00:08:14.066
We can see

00:08:14.066 --> 00:08:17.800
that there is an

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:19.200
interface at the connection between the ball and the spring.

00:08:19.466 --> 00:08:20.800
The number of interfaces

00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.800
determines how many balls there are on this spring.

00:08:23.900 --> 00:08:26.700
This interface is a special chemical structure

00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:28.233
called xylose

00:08:28.233 --> 00:08:29.866
, and bosera

00:08:29.866 --> 00:08:32.700
is a derivative of xylose.

00:08:32.800 --> 00:08:34.400
After it enters the skin,

00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:36.466
part of its body decomposes

00:08:36.466 --> 00:08:39.133
to synthesize this interface.

00:08:39.300 --> 00:08:41.533
When the number of synthesized interfaces increases,

00:08:41.533 --> 00:08:43.866
the number of balls generated increases.

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:44.900
In short,

00:08:44.900 --> 00:08:48.066
it is bosera. It uses part of its own body

00:08:48.066 --> 00:08:49.533
to help you synthesize interfaces

00:08:49.533 --> 00:08:51.200
to make your balls more.

00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:52.200
Each ball

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:53.300
is not empty, and

00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:55.000
it contains fillers.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.933
This filler is called glycosaminoglycan.

00:08:57.933 --> 00:09:00.266
After bosaminoglycan enters our skin,

00:09:00.266 --> 00:09:03.433
it can promote the production of glycosaminoglycan

00:09:03.433 --> 00:09:05.633
, which is the production of the filler of the ball.

00:09:05.633 --> 00:09:07.700
If more is produced,

00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:09.466
the ball will become bigger.

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:10.400
So

00:09:10.400 --> 00:09:11.933
if the number of balls increases and

00:09:11.933 --> 00:09:13.466
the individual balls become bigger,

00:09:13.466 --> 00:09:15.800
then our mattress will become thicker, and

00:09:15.800 --> 00:09:18.400
the elasticity and fullness of our dermis

00:09:18.400 --> 00:09:19.700
will increase. Does

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:21.066
it have anti-aging properties?

00:09:21.300 --> 00:09:24.133
Why is it said that bosaminoglycan can only repair

00:09:24.133 --> 00:09:26.066
but not anti-aging? It

00:09:26.200 --> 00:09:27.000
is because

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:31.433
it defines repair as a process of barrier thickening

00:09:31.433 --> 00:09:33.666
, but in fact it does not conflict with anti-aging

00:09:33.733 --> 00:09:34.333
. Anti-aging

00:09:34.333 --> 00:09:37.333
is always It is not something that can be solved by a single channel.

00:09:37.333 --> 00:09:40.333
It must be a very comprehensive solution.

00:09:40.333 --> 00:09:41.733
Our barrier becomes thicker,

00:09:41.733 --> 00:09:43.633
the skin's tolerance becomes stronger,

00:09:43.633 --> 00:09:44.733
the skin becomes firmer

00:09:44.733 --> 00:09:45.433
, fuller

00:09:45.433 --> 00:09:46.233
and more abundant.

00:09:46.233 --> 00:09:48.866
Isn't it also a means of anti-aging? What about the products

00:09:49.266 --> 00:09:49.900
on the market

00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:52.233
that have added the ingredient phosphene?

00:09:52.233 --> 00:09:53.866
Before 2022,

00:09:53.866 --> 00:09:55.833
only brands of the L'Oreal Group

00:09:55.833 --> 00:09:58.233
have products with this ingredient added phosphene.

00:09:58.233 --> 00:10:00.533
Based on my own experience, I

00:10:00.533 --> 00:10:03.533
will introduce to you several products that I think are very good

00:10:03.533 --> 00:10:05.266
that have added phosphene.

00:10:05.266 --> 00:10:06.700
I have put them at the end of the video

00:10:06.700 --> 00:10:07.800
and you can take them yourself.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:13.066
The third question

00:10:13.066 --> 00:10:14.200
: A friend said that

00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:16.633
he used two skin care products to rub mud.

00:10:16.633 --> 00:10:18.500
Is this skin care product in vain?

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:20.400
Let me give you the next conclusion.

00:10:20.400 --> 00:10:22.900
As long as you rub the mud off,

00:10:22.900 --> 00:10:23.866
it is in vain. Why is

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:26.866
it said that the mud is useless if you rub it off?

00:10:26.966 --> 00:10:29.700
Because the mud is the film formed by your product

00:10:29.700 --> 00:10:33.000
on the surface of your skin. This film contains

00:10:33.066 --> 00:10:35.233
all the effective ingredients

00:10:35.233 --> 00:10:36.500
of the product.

00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:37.600
If you rub it into

00:10:37.666 --> 00:10:40.233
strips and it falls off,

00:10:40.233 --> 00:10:41.833
it will not be on your face.

00:10:41.866 --> 00:10:43.233
How can it be useful?

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:47.000
Then why is it easy to rub mud when products are stacked?

00:10:47.033 --> 00:10:49.800
An important reason is that this product

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:51.500
contains an ingredient

00:10:51.600 --> 00:10:55.200
that can easily absorb oil and

00:10:55.200 --> 00:10:56.500
film-forming agents.

00:10:56.500 --> 00:10:58.033
Its own property

00:10:58.033 --> 00:10:59.500
is to wrap these film-forming agents and

00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:01.500
oils together.

00:11:01.766 --> 00:11:04.733
Then, when you rub your face,

00:11:04.800 --> 00:11:06.866
you just need to rub it off

00:11:06.866 --> 00:11:08.866
and it will pull these film-forming agents

00:11:08.866 --> 00:11:10.933
and oils down together.

00:11:11.300 --> 00:11:13.800
It is similar to the principle of rain

00:11:13.933 --> 00:11:15.433
. How does it rain?

00:11:15.433 --> 00:11:17.500
There is dust acting as a condensation nucleus

00:11:17.500 --> 00:11:20.300
, and it wraps a lot of water vapor.

00:11:20.300 --> 00:11:22.700
When it is heavy enough,

00:11:23.066 --> 00:11:24.466
rain falls.

00:11:24.466 --> 00:11:26.900
The property of this substance

00:11:26.900 --> 00:11:30.033
is
that it wraps enough film-forming agents and oils,

00:11:30.033 --> 00:11:32.000
and when you rub it, you give it an external force,

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.433
and it pulls

00:11:33.433 --> 00:11:35.333
all these things down together.

00:11:35.666 --> 00:11:37.500
The ingredient I am talking about

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:39.433
is ceramide, which

00:11:39.433 --> 00:11:40.866
is well known to everyone.

00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:43.933
When there is ceramide in your face cream,

00:11:43.933 --> 00:11:46.333
it is very easy to rub into mud.

00:11:46.466 --> 00:11:47.666
In addition to ceramide,

00:11:47.666 --> 00:11:49.733
there are some powdered inorganic substances

00:11:49.733 --> 00:11:51.066
that also have this property,

00:11:51.066 --> 00:11:53.400
such as silica, starch, talc,

00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:55.066
mica, montmorillonite, etc.,

00:11:55.066 --> 00:11:56.833
which are also very easy to rub into mud

00:11:57.033 --> 00:11:58.333
. So how to solve this problem

00:11:58.333 --> 00:11:59.300
? Actually, it is very simple

00:11:59.300 --> 00:12:00.800
. Just don't rub it.

00:12:00.800 --> 00:12:02.066
For

00:12:02.066 --> 00:12:03.500
example, if it is a facial cream,

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:05.266
we melt it in our hands and

00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:08.500
mix it evenly. Then press it on the face.

00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:09.300
Don't rub it.

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:11.233
As long as it stays on your face

00:12:11.233 --> 00:12:13.333
, it can still play its role.

00:12:13.400 --> 00:12:15.400
There is also a special case.

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:18.066
Even if it is not rubbed into mud and falls off,

00:12:18.066 --> 00:12:19.900
it is still useless.

00:12:19.933 --> 00:12:23.066
This situation is a typical ingredient conflict.

00:12:23.133 --> 00:12:25.433
For example, when the original essence of VC

00:12:25.433 --> 00:12:28.066
and all products containing alkaline thickeners

00:12:28.300 --> 00:12:29.866
are mixed together,

00:12:29.866 --> 00:12:31.100
the system will be destroyed

00:12:31.100 --> 00:12:33.433
, and the entire film-forming system will become fragments.

00:12:33.433 --> 00:12:36.666
You will feel that the film falls off like crumbs.

00:12:36.866 --> 00:12:38.733
So what are alkaline thickeners? They refer to

00:12:38.733 --> 00:12:41.300
those ingredients that must be in an alkaline environment

00:12:41.300 --> 00:12:42.266
to thicken

00:12:42.266 --> 00:12:44.100
and form a film

00:12:44.233 --> 00:12:46.533
. Typically, if you look for them in the formula table,

00:12:46.533 --> 00:12:48.300
As long as it says carbomer,

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:49.633
sodium polyacrylate, and

00:12:49.633 --> 00:12:51.433
hydroxypropyl methylcellulose,

00:12:51.433 --> 00:12:53.433
these are alkaline thickeners.

00:12:53.433 --> 00:12:54.633
When they encounter acid,

00:12:54.633 --> 00:12:56.433
such as the original form of vitamin C,

00:12:56.433 --> 00:12:58.800
such as salicylic acid, glycolic acid, etc.,

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:01.700
their film-forming and thickening properties will collapse.

00:13:01.933 --> 00:13:04.866
It will be reflected on your face as flakes and

00:13:04.866 --> 00:13:07.666
mud will fall off when you rub it. The solution to this problem

00:13:07.666 --> 00:13:10.300
is not to use these two types of products together,

00:13:10.300 --> 00:13:11.933
because no matter whether you rub it or not,

00:13:11.933 --> 00:13:14.100
the mud will come off, so it’s useless

00:13:14.200 --> 00:13:15.433
. For example,

00:13:15.433 --> 00:13:16.733
most of Johnson

00:13:16.733 --> 00:13:19.866
&amp; Johnson’s body lotions are thickened with carbomer,

00:13:19.933 --> 00:13:23.633
so don’t add VC powder for whitening.

